quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  90,1,"I swear by this city (Makkah);"
  90,2,"And you are free (from sin, and to punish the enemies of Islâm on the Day of the conquest) in this city (Makkah).{1}",footnotes:1:1
  90,3,"And by the begetter (i.e. Adam عليه السلام) and that which he begot (i.e. his progeny)."
  90,4,"Verily, We have created man in toil."
  90,5,"Does he think that none can overcome him?"
  90,6,"He says (boastfully): "I have wasted wealth in abundance!""
  90,7,"Does he think that none sees him?"
  90,8,"Have We not made for him two eyes,"
  90,9,"And a tongue and two lips?"
  90,10,"And shown him the two ways (good and evil)?"